b'[<p><i><b>UFC Fight Night: Santos vs. Anders</b></i> (also known as <i><b>UFC Fight Night 137</b></i>) was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event produced by the <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">Ultimate Fighting Championship</a> held on September 22, 2018 at <a href="/wiki/Gin%C3%A1sio_do_Ibirapuera" title="Gin\xc3\xa1sio do Ibirapuera">Gin\xc3\xa1sio do Ibirapuera</a> in <a href="/wiki/S%C3%A3o_Paulo" title="S\xc3\xa3o Paulo">S\xc3\xa3o Paulo</a>, <a href="/wiki/Brazil" title="Brazil">Brazil</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-FNS\xc3\xa3oPaulo_2-0"><a href="#cite_note-FNS\xc3\xa3oPaulo-2">[2]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>A light heavyweight bout between former <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/UFC_Light_Heavyweight_Championship" title="UFC Light Heavyweight Championship">UFC Light Heavyweight Championship</a> challenger <a href="/wiki/Glover_Teixeira" title="Glover Teixeira">Glover Teixeira</a> and <a href="/wiki/Jimi_Manuwa" title="Jimi Manuwa">Jimi Manuwa</a> was expected to serve as the event headliner.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-ME_3-0"><a href="#cite_note-ME-3">[3]</a></sup> However, Teixeira pulled out on August 14 due to a shoulder injury.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-4"><a href="#cite_note-4">[4]</a></sup> He was replaced by <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Thiago_Santos_(middleweight_fighter)" title="Thiago Santos (middleweight fighter)">Thiago Santos</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-5"><a href="#cite_note-5">[5]</a></sup> In turn, Manuwa pulled out on September 16 due to a torn hamstring and was replaced by <a href="/wiki/Eryk_Anders" title="Eryk Anders">Eryk Anders</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-6"><a href="#cite_note-6">[6]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-7"><a href="#cite_note-7">[7]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Mark_Godbeer" title="Mark Godbeer">Mark Godbeer</a> was briefly scheduled to face <a href="/wiki/Luis_Henrique_(fighter)" title="Luis Henrique (fighter)">Luis Henrique</a> at the event. However, Godbeer pulled out of the fight in early August citing injury and was replaced by promotional newcomer Ryan Spann.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-GodbeerOut_8-0"><a href="#cite_note-GodbeerOut-8">[8]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Neil_Magny" title="Neil Magny">Neil Magny</a> was scheduled to face <a href="/wiki/Alex_Oliveira_(fighter)" title="Alex Oliveira (fighter)">Alex Oliveira</a> at the event. However Magny was removed from the pairing on August 22 in favor of a matchup with <a href="/wiki/Santiago_Ponzinibbio" title="Santiago Ponzinibbio">Santiago Ponzinibbio</a> in November at <a href="/wiki/UFC_Fight_Night:_Magny_vs._Ponzinibbio" title="UFC Fight Night: Magny vs. Ponzinibbio">UFC Fight Night: Magny vs. Ponzinibbio</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-MagnyOut_9-0"><a href="#cite_note-MagnyOut-9">[9]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-10"><a href="#cite_note-10">[10]</a></sup> He was replaced by <a href="/wiki/Carlo_Pedersoli_Jr." title="Carlo Pedersoli Jr.">Carlo Pedersoli Jr.</a><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-PedIn_11-0"><a href="#cite_note-PedIn-11">[11]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Ketlen_Vieira" title="Ketlen Vieira">Ketlen Vieira</a> was expected to face former <a href="/wiki/Invicta_Fighting_Championships#Bantamweight_Championship" title="Invicta Fighting Championships">Invicta FC Bantamweight Champion</a> and <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/UFC_Women%27s_Featherweight_Championship" title="UFC Women\'s Featherweight Championship">UFC Women\'s Featherweight Championship</a> challenger <a href="/wiki/Tonya_Evinger" title="Tonya Evinger">Tonya Evinger</a> at the event. However on August 7, Vieira pulled out due to a knee injury.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-12"><a href="#cite_note-12">[12]</a></sup> Evinger was removed from the card and then rescheduled for a future event against a different opponent.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-13"><a href="#cite_note-13">[13]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/The_Ultimate_Fighter_Nations:_Canada_vs._Australia" title="The Ultimate Fighter Nations: Canada vs. Australia">The Ultimate Fighter: Nations</a> middleweight winner <a href="/wiki/Elias_Theodorou" title="Elias Theodorou">Elias Theodorou</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/The_Ultimate_Fighter:_Brazil_3" title="The Ultimate Fighter: Brazil 3">The Ultimate Fighter: Brazil 3</a> heavyweight winner <a href="/wiki/Ant%C3%B4nio_Carlos_J%C3%BAnior" title="Ant\xc3\xb4nio Carlos J\xc3\xbanior">Ant\xc3\xb4nio Carlos J\xc3\xbanior</a> at the event. However, J\xc3\xbanior pulled out on August 28 due to injury.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-14"><a href="#cite_note-14">[14]</a></sup> The pairing was left intact and rescheduled for <a href="/wiki/UFC_231" title="UFC 231">UFC 231</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-15"><a href="#cite_note-15">[15]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Elizeu_Zaleski_dos_Santos" title="Elizeu Zaleski dos Santos">Elizeu Zaleski dos Santos</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Belal_Muhammad_(fighter)" title="Belal Muhammad (fighter)">Belal Muhammad</a> at the event. However on September 14, it was announced that Muhammad pulled out due to injury and was replaced by promotional newcomer Luigi Vendramini.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-16"><a href="#cite_note-16">[16]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>At the weigh-ins, former <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/UFC_Bantamweight_Championship" title="UFC Bantamweight Championship">UFC Bantamweight Champion</a> <a href="/wiki/Renan_Bar%C3%A3o" title="Renan Bar\xc3\xa3o">Renan Bar\xc3\xa3o</a> weighed in at 141.6 pounds, 5 pounds over the bantamweight non-title fight limit of 136. Bar\xc3\xa3o was fined 30 percent of his purse, which went to his opponent Andre Ewell.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-17"><a href="#cite_note-17">[17]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-18"><a href="#cite_note-18">[18]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The following fighters received $50,000 bonuses:<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-19"><a href="#cite_note-19">[19]</a></sup>\n</p>]'